Hecks.hecksagon "Consolidation" do
  # ============================================================
  # CONSOLIDATION — production hecksagon for the i75 PM retirement
  # ============================================================
  #
  # Pairs with body/sleep/consolidation/consolidation.bluebook. The
  # bluebook declares the PM (light/deep/final_light → fan-out into
  # four step commands) ; this file declares the persistence adapter
  # those commands route through.
  #
  # ---- :heki adapter -------------------------------------------
  #
  # The step commands the PM dispatches (Store.PromoteSignal,
  # Synapse.Compost, Remains.RecordRemains) all land on per-aggregate
  # heki stores under $INFO :
  #
  #   $INFO/store/store.heki                     ← PromoteSignal
  #   $INFO/synapse/synapse.heki                 ← Compost (mark)
  #   $INFO/remains/remains.heki                 ← RecordRemains
  #
  # The runtime resolves :heki adapter against the world's `dir`
  # config, so this hecksagon's adapter declaration just names :heki ;
  # the world (run-loop's --target dir) supplies the path. Same shape
  # body/dream/lucid_dream.hecksagon uses.
  #
  # ---- No :llm adapter -----------------------------------------
  #
  # Narrative emission stays templated rather than LLM-generated. The
  # consolidation narrative line — counts substituted from sibling
  # aggregate state via the cross-aggregate scaffolder (PR #581) —
  # rides the `:impression` attribute on Consciousness.DreamPulse.
  # No claude call ; the grounded counts ARE the poetry. Detail-mode
  # by design : NREM is work, not imagery (REM owns the imagery via
  # body/dream/dream.hecksagon's :dream_image adapter).
  #
  # ---- Activation status (i225 closed) -------------------------
  #
  # Pre-i225 : the Rust runtime parsed :heki adapters but did not
  # drive the PM's dispatches into multi-record sweep semantics ;
  # body/consolidate.sh remained as a transitional adapter doing
  # the actual store + remains growth.
  #
  # Post-i225 : the runtime sweep primitive lands —
  # `for_each: { from: "Aggregate.cold" }` enumerates the named
  # query at dispatch time and fires the receiving command once per
  # record. The Consolidation PM's NREM self-loops now produce
  # store + remains heki growth declaratively ; consolidate.sh is
  # retired (see body/shutdown/shutdown.hecksagon for the parallel
  # `:final_consolidation` adapter retirement).

  adapter :heki                      # cross-process persistence — store, remains grow here
end
